This paper deals with the privacy concerns related to personal data trading, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a framework for trading personal data, which involves budget allocation and arbitrage-freeness, indicating a connection to databases (cs.DB) and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the personalized nature of privacy loss, which could be related to cyberpsychology (cs.CY) and social networks (cs.SI).
